Effects of underreporting

Andrea Brizzi

06/04/2021

The objective of this markdown is to introduce the component of underreporting in our SEIR simulations. This means that we are not able to observe the actual number of new infections \((I_t)\), rather we only see a proportion \(\pi\) of these. In particular, we assume that since the 3rd week onwards, the number of cases is: \[ y_t \sim \text{Binom}(I_t, \pi). \] The question is: does it still make sense to make use of Megan approximation in these settings?

We will start by considering a reporting rate of \(\pi = 50 \%\).

sims_SEIR <- readRDS(file.path(data_path, "sims_SEIR"))
names <- names(sims_SEIR)

# generation interval parameters
mean_si <- 6.5
sd_si <- sqrt(3^2 + 3.5^2)

# reporting rate
pi <- 0.5

Let’s a code!

# Problems showing plots: maybe store them in a list
list_plots <- list()
final_stats <- data.frame(method = as.character(),
                          coverage = as.numeric(),
                          scenario = as.character(),
                          CIwidth = as.numeric())

estimated_starts <- data.frame(scenario = as.character(),
                               estimate = as.numeric())

for (name in names[3:8]){
  
  # Transform the data
  df <- as.data.frame(sims_SEIR[[name]])
  df$day <- 1:(dim(df)[1])
  
  # Now cut off 2 weeks of data
  df <- filter(df, day > 2*7)
  
  results <- data.frame(sim = as.numeric(),
                        method = as.character(),
                        R0 = as.numeric(),
                        lowR0 = as.numeric(),
                        upR0 = as.numeric())
  
  
  # For every possible simulation
  for(c in 1:(ncol(df - 1))){
    
    # Get incidence
    incidence <- data.frame(cases = df[,c])
    incidence$cases <- rbinom(n = length(incidence$cases),
                              size = incidence$cases,
                              prob = pi)
    incidence$day <- 2*7 + 1:dim(incidence)[1]
    
    # Make sure there are cases in the first 2 observed weeks...
    somecases <- (sum(incidence$cases[1:14]) >= 10)
    
    if (somecases){
      #== simple EpiEstim: biweekly sliding window
      
      epestim <- epiestim(incidence[1:14,], mean_GT = mean_si, sd_GT = sd_si)
    
      results <- rbind(results, data.frame(
        sim = c, method = 'simpleEpiEstim', R0 = epestim[1],
        lowR0 = epestim[2], upR0 = epestim[3]
      ))
      
      
      #== Linear Exponential Growth: estimate using first 2 weeks 
      if(any(incidence$cases==0)){
        incidence$casesC <- incidence$cases+0.5
        incidence$logcases <- log(incidence$casesC)
      }else{
        incidence$logcases <- log(incidence$cases)
      }
      
      eglin <- EG_Lin(data = incidence[1:14,], mean_GT = mean_si, sd_GT = sd_si)
      
      results <- rbind(results, data.frame(
        sim = c, method = 'EgLin', R0 = eglin[1],
        lowR0 = eglin[2], upR0 = eglin[3]
      ))
      
      
     
      #== EpiEstim with corrections
      
      ## Only Megan's
      epestim2 <- epiestim_andrea(data = incidence[1:14,], mean_GT = mean_si, sd_GT = sd_si, andrea = FALSE)

      tmp <- data.frame(scenario = name,
                        estimate = epestim2$estimated_start)
      estimated_starts <- rbind(estimated_starts, tmp)
      
      epestim2 <- epestim2$results
      results <- rbind(results, data.frame(
          sim = c, method = 'EpiEstim_Megan', R0 = epestim2[1],
          lowR0 = epestim2[2], upR0 = epestim2[3]
      ))

      ## Mine as well
      epestim2 <- epiestim_andrea(data = incidence[1:14,], mean_GT = mean_si, sd_GT = sd_si, andrea = TRUE)
      
      epestim2 <- epestim2$results
      results <- rbind(results, data.frame(
          sim = c, method = 'EpiEstim_Andrea', R0 = epestim2[1],
          lowR0 = epestim2[2], upR0 = epestim2[3]
      ))
      
      if(if.plots){
        
        true_R0 <- as.numeric(stringr::str_match(name, "R0=\\s*(.*?)\\s*pop")[2])
        true_pop <-as.numeric(stringr::str_split(name, "=")[[1]][3])
        
        dfR <- data.frame(y = true_R0*(1 - cumsum( incidence2$cases)/true_pop),
                          x = 1:length(incidence2$cases))
        
        
        ggplot() +
          geom_line(data = epestim$R, aes(x = t_end + 14, y = `Median(R)`), col = "blue") +
          geom_ribbon(data = epestim$R, aes(x = t_end + 14, 
                                            ymin = `Quantile.0.975(R)`,
                                            ymax = `Quantile.0.025(R)`), alpha = .5, fill = "blue") + 
          geom_line(data = epestim2$R, aes(x = t_end + start - 1, y = `Median(R)`), col = "red") + 
          geom_ribbon(data = epestim2$R, aes(x = t_end + start - 1, 
                                             ymin = `Quantile.0.975(R)`,
                                             ymax = `Quantile.0.025(R)`), alpha = .5, fill = "red") + 
          xlab("days since start") + xlim(0, 70) + geom_line(data = dfR, aes(x = x, y = y), col = 'grey')
          ggtitle("Performance of EpiEstim with and without adjustement")
      }
    }
    }
    
    
  rownames(results) <- c()
  
  
  # show results:
  trueR0 <- as.numeric(stringr::str_match(name, "R0=\\s*(.*?)\\s*pop")[2])
  
  results$method <- as.factor(results$method)
  results <- results %>% group_by(method)
  
  # This is stupid but otherwise I can t get it to work:
  if(trueR0 == 2){
    gg <- ggplot(data = results, aes(y = R0, x = method)) + geom_boxplot() +
    geom_hline(aes(yintercept = 2),col = "red", linetype = "dashed") + ggtitle(name)
  }
  if(trueR0 == 2.5){
    gg <- ggplot(data = results, aes(y = R0, x = method)) + geom_boxplot() +
    geom_hline(aes(yintercept = 2.5),col = "red", linetype = "dashed") + ggtitle(name)
  }
    if(trueR0 == 3){
    gg <- ggplot(data = results, aes(y = R0, x = method)) + geom_boxplot() +
    geom_hline(aes(yintercept = 3),col = "red", linetype = "dashed") + ggtitle(name)
  }
  
  
  list_plots[[name]] <- gg
  ggsave(plot = gg, filename = file.path(plots_path, paste0("underreporting_.5",name, ".png")))
  
  results$inside <- (trueR0 <= results$upR0 & trueR0 >= results$lowR0)
  results$CIwidth <- results$upR0 - results$lowR0

  tmp <- results %>% group_by(method) %>%
    summarise(coverage = mean(inside), scenario = name, CIwidth = mean(CIwidth))
  
  final_stats <- rbind(final_stats, tmp)
  rm(aaa)
}
